From f67e116420d871aa69f8c7d9db203d443f6d903c Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Dmitry Baryshkov <dmitry.baryshkov@oss.qualcomm.com>
Date: Tue, 17 Feb 2026 23:20:42 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 166/194] HACK! clk: qcom: dispcc-sdm845: set
 GENPD_FLAG_NO_STAY_ON flag for MDSS domain

Since the commit 13a4b7fb6260 ("pmdomain: core: Leave powered-on genpds
on until late_initcall_sync") setting of the display clocks is partially
broken. For example, when on SDM845-HDK the bootloader leaves display
enabled, later the kernel can't set up DSI clocks, ending up with the
broken display, blinking blue.

Fixes the following errors that happened in poco f1 with tianma panel in
prior kernel versions like 6.19 or 7.0 and causing display to not work.
but in 7.1rc, the crash didnt seem to happen, but the display was facing
iommu errors and video out timeout issues causing panel to not work for 20s
during boot up instead. But this commit fixes the display to work properly.
Although I get two other crashes that "dsi0_phy_pll_out_dsiclk already disabled"
and "dsi0_phy_pll_out_dsiclk already unprepared" with this commit.
But these doesnt cause 20s delay or iommu errors or any other issues.
So for now keeping it as a workaround/hack.

